description: Try our easy to follow Stand 'N Stuff Prawns recipe. Absolutely delicious with the best ingredients from Woolworths.
keywords: Prawn dishes,Low saturated fat,Prawn,Tree nut free,Egg free,Low sugar,Sesame free,Microwave,High protein,High fibre,Soy free,Quick & easy lunch,Low fat,Peanut free
name: Stand 'N Stuff Prawns Recipe | Woolworths
recipeIngredient: 0.5 cup Old El Paso Mild Taco Sauce
28g Old El Paso taco spice mix
8 Old El Paso stand’n stuff tortillas

recipeInstructions.text: Toss prawns in Taco Spice Mix to coat. Heat a little oil in a large frying pan over mediumhigh heat. Cook prawns, in two batches, for 3 to 4 minutes or until prawns are pink and cooked through. Transfer to a plate, cover with foil to keep warm.

For warm Tortillas: Remove tortillas from pack and divide into 2 stacks. Microwave: on HIGH/1100 watts/100% power for 20 seconds* Oven: wrap in foil & heat in a preheated oven at 180°C (160°C fan forced) for 7 minutes. DO NOT HEAT TORTILLAS IN THE PLASTIC PACKAGE *Times may vary depending on microwave wattage.

Place corn cobs on microwave plate and microwave for 3 minutes on high. Remove from microwave and discard husk. Spray a chargrill or large fry pan with a little oil and place over high heat. Add corn and cook, turning for 34 minutes or until kernels are tender and slightly charred. Cut kernels from corn and combine with cabbage and coriander. Toss with lime juice, oil and sprinkle with feta. Top with Old El Paso taco sauce
